column5: I just checked Winnipeg for rental cars and they have a ton for mid June at very low prices. Previously, this was not the case. If you are looking at going to Canada for a trip, you might want to check Winnipeg as a flight option. Sadly, cars at INL are still scarce and very expensive.
Would love for Winnipeg to open up flight options out of Denver. MSP is the only option right now and doesn't work for our group. Best of luck!
Are you only interested in non stop?
yes. I know you can get to Winnipeg through MSP. The flight to Winnipeg works, the flight home doesn't. We can't get to Winnipeg from camp for the 1p departure to MSP.
